  "name": "Dual Initiative [Mythic]",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/tools/navigation/hourglass-yellow.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The creature gets two turns each round, one on its initiative count and another on its initiative count &ndash; 20. For example, if the monster&rsquo;s initiative is 23, on its first turn it could make a full attack (and take a 5-foot step) at initiative 23, and on its second turn at initiative 3 it could take a move action and cast a spell. This allows the monster to perform two actions per round that normally take an entire round, such as using a <a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; color: #ff6400; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.spells\" data-id=\"kyo0kwhw2jhuztju\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">summon monster</span></a> spell. For the purposes of spells and effects that have a duration of a round or longer or trigger at the beginning of the creature&rsquo;s round or the start of its turn (such as saving throws against ongoing effects or taking bleed damage), only the monster&rsquo;s first turn each round counts toward such durations.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Format</em>: 21</p>\n<p><em>Location</em>: Init.</p>",
